Here's the full setup:

**XAML — wrap CollectionView in RefreshView for pull-to-refresh:**

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                           WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1"
                           Text="{Binding Name}"
                           VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <Label Text="No items found."
                   HorizontalOptions="Center"
                   VerticalOptions="Center" />
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel (using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm):**

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    public ObservableCollection<Item> Items { get; } = new();

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelected()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;

        await _nav.GoToAsync(nameof(DetailPage),
            new Dictionary<string, object> { { "Item", CurrentItem } });

        // Clear selection so same item can be re-selected later
        CurrentItem = null;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Refresh()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            Items.Clear();
            foreach (var item in data)
                Items.Add(item);
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // Must set false to hide spinner
        }
    }
}
```

**Key binding points:**

| XAML Property | VM Property | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `SelectedItem` | `CurrentItem` (TwoWay) | Tracks which item is tapped |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires navigation on select |
| `IsRefreshing` | `IsRefreshing` (TwoWay) | Controls the refresh spinner |
| `RefreshView.Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Triggers API reload |
| `ItemsSource` | `Items` (ObservableCollection) | Auto-updates UI on add/remove |

**Critical details:**
- Use `ObservableCollection<T>`, never `List<T>` — otherwise the UI won't update.
- Set `IsRefreshing = false` in a `finally` block so the spinner always stops.
- Reset `CurrentItem = null` after navigation so the same item can be re-selected.
- Always set `x:DataType` on `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
